    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Key Battles</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Goliad Campaign</h2><ul><li>Mexican forces capture Texan troops at Goliad</li><li>Controversial execution of Texan prisoners by Mexican army</li><li>Galvanized Texan resistance and international sympathy</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Goliad Massacre, where captured Texan soldiers were executed, intensified anger against Mexico and strengthened Texan resolve to fight for independence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Colonel James Fannin’s surrender led to the massacre of his troops.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss the impact of the Goliad Massacre on Texan and international opinion.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing the Goliad Massacre with the Alamo siege.</p></div></div>",
