    "id": "slide7",
    "eyebrow": "Key Battles",
    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Key Battles</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Battle of San Jacinto</h2><ul><li>April 21, 1836: Decisive Texan victory under Sam Houston</li><li>Captured Mexican President Santa Anna</li><li>Effectively ended the Texas War of Independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Battle of San Jacinto was the final major battle where Texan forces defeated the Mexican army and captured Santa Anna, securing Texas independence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Sam Houston’s surprise attack led to a swift and overwhelming victory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate how the Battle of San Jacinto changed the course of the war.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the battle’s speed and decisiveness.</p></div></div>",
