      "h": "Multiple Perspectives on the Revolution",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> The revolution involved multiple perspectives: Texans fighting for autonomy, Mexico defending sovereignty, and indigenous groups impacted by the conflict and territorial changes.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; guides.loc.gov. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Texans sought independence and self-governance</li><li>Mexican government aimed to maintain territorial integrity</li><li>Indigenous peoples affected but often marginalized in records</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Many indigenous tribes were displaced or caught between Texan and Mexican forces.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Compare how different groups experienced the Texas Revolution.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Ignoring indigenous perspectives or oversimplifying Mexican motives.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; guides.loc.gov <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p>"
