    "num": "12",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Check Your Understanding: Causes and Early Events</h2><ul><li>What political changes in Mexico contributed to the Texas Revolution?</li><li>How did social and economic factors influence Texan settlers?</li><li>Why were early battles like Gonzales important?</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This checkpoint reviews key causes and early events of the Texas War of Independence to reinforce understanding before moving to later topics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Recall Mexico’s shift to centralism and the Battle of Gonzales as examples.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Answer the questions and reflect on how these factors interconnect.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Separating causes and events instead of seeing their connections.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide12\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which battle is considered the decisive victory that secured Texas independence?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Siege of the Alamo&quot;,&quot;Battle of Goliad&quot;,&quot;Battle of San Jacinto&quot;,&quot;Battle of Gonzales&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:2,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The Battle of San Jacinto was the decisive battle where Texan forces defeated Santa Anna&#39;s army, effectively securing Texas independence.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the significance of the Texas Declaration of Independence in the context of the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should describe the political and legal importance of the declaration, its role in formalizing Texas&#39; break from Mexico, and its impact on the war effort.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texas Declaration of Independence formally announced Texas&#39; separation from Mexico, outlining grievances against Mexican rule and justifying the revolution. It united Texan settlers politically and provided a legal basis for the establishment of the Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;It declared Texas independent from Mexico and listed reasons for the revolution&quot;,&quot;It was a formal political document that justified the war and helped unify Texans&quot;,&quot;It established the Republic of Texas and set the stage for governance after independence&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
