    "eyebrow": "Military Campaigns",
    "num": "16",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Military Campaigns</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Goliad Campaign: Tragedy and Impact</h2><ul><li>Texan forces captured Presidio La Bahía at Goliad</li><li>Mexican troops under General Urrea defeated Texans at Coleto Creek</li><li>Captured Texans executed in the Goliad Massacre</li><li>Event intensified Texan resolve against Mexico</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Goliad Campaign ended tragically with the execution of Texan prisoners, an event that shocked settlers and increased support for the revolution. It highlighted the brutal nature of the conflict and Mexican determination to suppress rebellion. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The massacre was used alongside the Alamo to rally Texan forces with the slogan 'Remember Goliad!'</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how the Goliad Massacre affected Texan morale and recruitment.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing the Goliad Massacre with the Battle of the Alamo or underestimating its emotional impact.</p></div></div>",
