      "secnum": "Deep Dive 16",
      "h": "The Goliad Massacre’s Role in the Revolution",
      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> The Goliad Campaign ended tragically with the execution of Texan prisoners, an event that shocked settlers and increased support for the revolution. It highlighted the brutal nature of the conflict and Mexican determination to suppress rebellion.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; thc.texas.gov; history.com. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Texan forces captured Presidio La Bahía at Goliad</li><li>Mexican troops under General Urrea defeated Texans at Coleto Creek</li><li>Captured Texans executed in the Goliad Massacre</li><li>Event intensified Texan resolve against Mexico</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>The massacre was used alongside the Alamo to rally Texan forces with the slogan 'Remember Goliad!'</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Explain how the Goliad Massacre affected Texan morale and recruitment.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Confusing the Goliad Massacre with the Battle of the Alamo or underestimating its emotional impact.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; thc.texas.gov; history.com <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup></p>"
