    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Developments</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Establishing the Republic of Texas</h2><ul><li>Interim government formed post-independence</li><li>Sam Houston elected first president in 1836</li><li>Constitution modeled on U.S. principles</li><li>Challenges included defense, diplomacy, and economy</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Following independence, Texas leaders quickly organized a government to manage internal affairs and seek international recognition. The Republic faced immediate challenges in securing borders and establishing legitimacy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Houston’s presidency focused on stabilizing the republic and negotiating with Native American tribes and the U.S.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> List two major challenges the Republic of Texas faced after independence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming the Republic was immediately stable and recognized by other nations.</p></div></div>",
