    "num": "19",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Perspectives</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texan, Mexican, and Indigenous Perspectives</h2><ul><li>Texans sought self-governance and protection of rights</li><li>Mexican government viewed rebellion as illegal insurrection</li><li>Indigenous peoples faced displacement and shifting alliances</li><li>Tejanos experienced divided loyalties and cultural challenges</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Revolution involved multiple groups with differing goals and experiences. Understanding these perspectives reveals the complexity of the conflict beyond a simple binary struggle. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Tejanos supported independence, while others remained loyal to Mexico, complicating social dynamics.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare the motivations of Texans and Mexicans during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying the conflict as only Anglo settlers versus Mexican forces.</p></div></div>",
