    "eyebrow": "Historical Interpretation",
    "num": "23",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">23</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Interpretation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Contested Narratives and Historical Debate</h2><ul><li>Differing Texan and Mexican accounts of battles and events</li><li>Debates over causes and motivations of the revolution</li><li>Challenges in interpreting indigenous and Tejano roles</li><li>Importance of critical source evaluation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Historical interpretations of the Texas Revolution vary, reflecting national perspectives and incomplete records. Recognizing these disagreements is key to developing a balanced understanding. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Mexican sources often portray Santa Anna as defending national sovereignty, contrasting with Texan views of him as a tyrant.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify one area where Texan and Mexican historical narratives differ.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting a single perspective without considering alternative viewpoints.</p></div></div>",
