    "num": "25",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">25</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interpreting Texan Letters During the Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texan leaders’ letters reveal motivations and challenges</li><li>Express concerns about Mexican policies and independence</li><li>Highlight personal and political stakes in the conflict</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Letters from Texan leaders provide firsthand insight into the political and emotional context of the revolution. They reveal the urgency and complexity of the independence movement. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from Sam Houston discusses the need for unity among Texan settlers to resist Mexican control.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze an excerpt from a Texan leader’s letter and identify key concerns expressed about Mexican governance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming letters are purely propaganda without considering personal and political context.</p></div></div>",
