    "eyebrow": "Historical Debate",
    "num": "27",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Debate</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Contested Narratives of the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texan and Mexican accounts often differ significantly</li><li>Disputes over causes, conduct, and outcomes persist</li><li>Critical analysis helps uncover biases and perspectives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Revolution’s history is marked by conflicting narratives from Texan and Mexican viewpoints. Understanding these differences is key to a balanced interpretation of events. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texan sources emphasize heroism at the Alamo, while Mexican accounts highlight military discipline and order.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare two differing accounts of the same battle and identify contrasting perspectives.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting one-sided narratives without questioning source bias.</p></div></div>",
