    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Social and Cultural Impact</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Effects of the Revolution on Tejanos and Indigenous Peoples</h2><ul><li>Tejanos faced suspicion and displacement during and after the war</li><li>Indigenous groups experienced loss of land and autonomy</li><li>Historical records often underrepresent these groups’ experiences</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Revolution had profound social and cultural consequences for Tejanos and indigenous peoples, many of which remain underexplored in historical narratives. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Tejanos supported independence, but many were caught between loyalties and suffered reprisals.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss challenges in reconstructing the experiences of Tejanos and indigenous peoples during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the diversity of experiences among Tejanos and indigenous groups.</p></div></div>",
