    "num": "34",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">34</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing the Texas Declaration of Independence</h2><ul><li>Declaration outlines grievances against Mexican government</li><li>Asserts right to self-governance and independence</li><li>Reflects political philosophy and legal reasoning of the time</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texas Declaration of Independence is a foundational document expressing the political rationale for Texas’s break from Mexico, combining legal arguments with appeals to justice. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The declaration cites violations of rights and laws as justification for independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key grievances listed in the declaration and their significance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Reading the declaration as purely symbolic without legal context.</p></div></div>",
